<B>Show Overview</B><BR>
See the latest technology from the leaders in computer medical visualization. Visit
the Silicon Graphics booth at RSNA and and experience the latest solutions
that have set the pace for visualization in the medical industry.
See demos on all Silicon Graphics computer systems including; 
<A HREF="/Products/hardware/desktop/products/">O2</A>,
<A HREF="/Products/hardware/desktop/products/">OCTANE</A>, 
<A HREF="/Products/hardware/graphics/">Onyx2</A>
and the 
<A HREF="/Products/hardware/servers/products/Origin200.html">Origin200</A>
product line.
<P>
Meet the solution providers at the
Silicon Graphics booth. See how various Silicon Graphics partners are using SGI Systems 
and applications to provide the latest in technology
for today's medical field, focusing on the following areas:
<P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="5" CELLPADDING="5" BORDER="0"><TR VALIGN="TOP"><TD>
<IMG SRC="telemedicine.jpg" WIDTH="155" HEIGHT="155" ALIGN="LEFT">
<BR>&nbsp;<BR>
</TD><TD>
<IMG SRC="telemedicine_title.gif" WIDTH="226" HEIGHT="18"><BR>
Silicon Graphics solutions permit a health care professional to share
information in real time with colleagues within the hospital or even in
other cities. The use of the of the internet and intranet have enhanced
telemedicine by allowing visual and audio communication to be used to
provide diagnostic and consultative support for practitioners, directly
deliver medical care to patients at distance sites and give the
consulting physician a clear understanding of the patient's condition.
</TD></TR><TR VALIGN="TOP"><TD>
<IMG SRC="review.jpg" WIDTH="155" HEIGHT="155" ALIGN="LEFT">
<BR>&nbsp;<BR>
</TD><TD>
<IMG SRC="review_title.gif" WIDTH="188" HEIGHT="18"><BR>
Radiologist and physicians can now examine complex anatomical features and
their interrelationships using a Silicon Graphics system that
responds at interactive rates. They can view anatomy in three dimensions,
rotate images, and differentiate values. Diagnostic images can be
segmented, window-leveled, and better analyzed. Multiple data sets can be
combined or compared.
</TD></TR><TR VALIGN="TOP"><TD>
<IMG SRC="archiving.jpg" WIDTH="155" HEIGHT="155" ALIGN="LEFT">
<BR>&nbsp;<BR>
</TD><TD>
<IMG SRC="archiving_title.gif" WIDTH="147" HEIGHT="18"><BR>
Silicon Graphics offers solutions that include industry leading graphics
storage and display technology. Our systems make it simple for
professionals to capture images in high-resolution digital formats. Once
stored electronically, images are protected from physical damage and
degradation and can be accessed quickly from locations throughout the
hospital.
</TD></TR><TR VALIGN="TOP"><TD>
<IMG SRC="surgical_sim.jpg" WIDTH="155" HEIGHT="155" ALIGN="LEFT">
<BR>&nbsp;<BR>
</TD><TD>
<IMG SRC="surgical_title.gif" WIDTH="273" HEIGHT="18"><BR>
Simulated procedures will allow surgeons to train, practice, and familiarize
themselves with new techniques in a more realistic environment. Silicon
Graphics virtual reality solutions can create life like simulations that let
surgeons interact with the complexity of a living human being in tactile,
visual surroundings. One trend in health care today is minimally invasive
surgery. New endoscopic techniques are dramatically reducing the cost of
surgical procedures, and the risk to the patient. But the needed hand-eye
skills demand considerable training time, which can limit the low-cost
techniques. Simulation training provides a solution.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>&nbsp;
<P>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
